@node Overview "Overview"
@{!</PRE>}I have some web pages setup, with my email info on them.  The problem is that when I'm at uni I can't check any email thats been sent to my home address, and when I'm at home (uni holidays) the uni closes our accounts, so any mail going there is lost.@{!<P>}
While I'm at uni I have my uni email address on my webpages, and when I come home I have to change it to my home address.  This wasn't so bad before, but now I have around 40 pages, each with my email address at least twice, so its a bit of a pain changing them by hand.@{!<P>}
There are other programs that replace strings in files but, like they say, none had all the features I wanted, so I thought I'd write my own.
@endnode

@node Use "Use"
@{!</PRE>}Just enter the strings, select a file, and click go!@{!<P>}

No mouse is needed - use TAB to move between the input strings and to select the "Do it" button
@endnode

